          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Exceeding.—Literally, unto height, upwards; an adverbial expression, which frequently occurs in the Chronicles. (See 1Chronicles 14:2 : “On high.”)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Exceeding.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "unto height, upwards;",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " an adverbial expression, which frequently occurs in the Chronicles. (See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 14:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " : “On high.”)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Of fame and of glory throughout all countries.—Literally, for a name and for a glory (tiph’ereth) for all the lands. (Comp. Isaiah 2:3; Isaiah 60:3, et seq., Isaiah 62:2-3.) In similar terms the famous Assyrian Sennacherib (Sin-ahi-irba) speaks of his palace as built “for the lodging (taprati) of multitudes of men.” And of his temple of Nergal he says: “The house of Nergal, within the city of Tarbiçu, I caused to be made, and like day I caused it to shine” (usnammir).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Of fame and of glory throughout all",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "countries.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "for a name and for a glory ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(",
            "children": []
          },
