            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I will therefore now make preparation for it.—Literally, Let me now prepare for him—the expression of an earnest desire, and self-encouragement to an arduous task, rather than of mere resolve.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "I will therefore now make preparation for it.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Let me now prepare for him",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—the expression of an earnest desire, and self-encouragement ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "to",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " an arduous task, rather than of mere resolve.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "We need not suppose that the verse relates to any actual utterance of David’s. It is not said when nor to whom he spoke. The historian is merely representing the king’s motive for these preparations. “To say” in Hebrew often means to think, by an elliptic construction. (Comp. Exodus 2:14 with Genesis 17:17.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "We need not suppose that the verse relates to any actual utterance of David’s. It is not said when nor to whom he spoke. The historian is merely representing the king’s motive for these preparations. “To say” in Hebrew often means ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "to think,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " by an elliptic construction. (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 2:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " with ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 17:17",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "So David prepared.—It is strange, but instructive, to remember that there have been critics so destitute of the historical faculty as to allege that “the whole episode about David’s preparations is a fiction of the chronist’s” (Gramberg), because the Books of Samuel and Kings are silent on the subject.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "So David prepared.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—It is strange, but instructive, to remember that there have been critics so destitute of the historical faculty as to allege that “the whole episode about David’s preparations is a fiction of the chronist’s” (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Gramberg",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ")",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
